<section xml:id="subsec-1-3-1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <p>Two statements are the same whenever they have the same truth value. Is <m>[P\implies Q]\equiv [(</m>~<m>P)\vee Q]</m>?</p>
    <p></p>
    <p></p>
    <figure>
        <tabular halign="center">
          <row header="yes" bottom="minor" >
            <cell><m>P</m></cell>
            <cell><m>Q</m></cell>
            <cell><m>(P\implies Q)</m></cell>
            <cell>~<m>P</m></cell>
            <cell><m>[(</m>~<m>P)\vee Q]</m></cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>T</cell>
            <cell>T</cell>
            <cell><em>T</em></cell>
            <cell>F</cell>
            <cell><em>T</em></cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>T</cell>
            <cell>F</cell>
            <cell><em>F</em></cell>
            <cell>F</cell>
            <cell><em>F</em></cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>F</cell>
            <cell>T</cell>
            <cell><em>T</em></cell>
            <cell>T</cell>
            <cell><em>T</em></cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>F</cell>
            <cell>F</cell>
            <cell><em>T</em></cell>
            <cell>T</cell>
            <cell><em>T</em></cell>
          </row>
        </tabular>
      
    </figure>
    <p> Thus we see that the truth values are the same for <m>[P\implies Q]</m> and <m>[(</m>~<m>P)\vee Q]</m>!</p>

</section>